5. RMP SUBMITTAL

Submittal of an RMP is required for all covered processes for which a regulated substance is above a threshold quantity in a process.     A completed RMP registration is included in Appendix A. In addition, the certification letter to be included with the RMP submittal is provided in Appendix B. 

Upon submittal of the RMP, no additional submittals will be required by KKGP under RMP until:

1.	A flammable gases/vapor cloud explosion accident with offsite impacts occurs;
2.	Process changes might reasonably be expected to change the distance to the level of concern by a factor of two or more;
3.	A change occurs at or near facility that requires a revised offsite consequence analysis (eg. New public receptors move within the impact radius), or;  
4.	Five years from the date of renewal submittal of the RMP.


The certification letter and the electronic submittal should be submitted through RMP*eSubmit.
